</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-C1EFD393-088C-432B-A56C-F359BAB2BFC6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluation/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">-
</p></section><section id="GUID-915CF84E-F2F9-4FBB-B5B5-F735CB33A661" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">The build up of a printed image is done is both directions of the carriage movement (Bi-Directional). Bi-directional errors might be caused by an incorrect media thickness. Therefore, the thickness of the media is determined as part of the media calibration.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p ">During this calibration lines are printed from left to right and from right to left and the distances between these lines is measured over the width of the media. This bidirectional error will be corrected after this calibration.
</p></section><example id="GUID-11499A37-E18C-4D23-BC34-49840D0E7CF6" class="- topic/example "><p class="- topic/p "> 
